Details

Job Posting Title:   SE_Embedded Software Application Engineer_Specialist
Description:   Embedded SW developer, Specialist

About the role
At Connectivity, we are leading the development of in-vehicle connectivity-based solutions for the whole Volvo Group. As a vital part of the functional growth in Electromobility and Automation, we implement end-to-end functions of different tailor-made connected truck services available through Dynafleet services and Volvo Connect App such as Driver Coaching, I-See, Remote SW Download, Vehicle apps, and Geofencing.

We are entering an exciting new technology transformation with focus on new development and are therefore now looking for an Embedded Software Developer with excellent technical expertise who wants to join our collaborative and passionate team. With us, you’ll get the opportunity to build up the future vehicle connectivity platform and make your mark on our digital transformation.

Additional responsibilities are:
•       Share knowledge with colleagues and contribute to our communities of practice
•       Drive investigations on new technology
•       Carry out requirement-and subsystem verification tasks together with the team

We are looking for...
A Software Developer with excellent technical expertise.
Agile product development is where the candidate thrives. Inspiring, developing, and motivating colleagues are a natural part of the role. Strong technical passion and drive is required and makes the candidate to a natural leader of challenging tasks demanding to explore new knowledge areas. With customer-focused approach, the candidate is passionate about creating the best customer solutions and experiences.

Requirements:
•       Master’s degree in Information Technology or Computer Engineering or equivalent education/experience.
•       8 years experiences in modern C++ development
•       3+ years experiences of product development within Telematics (or related knowledge area)
•       Python
•       Yocto/Open embedded
•       3+ years in software architecture
•       Embedded Linux, basic configuration, applying patches and debugging
•       Fluent in English, both verbal and written.

Additionally, we highly value the experience of communication protocols (such as MQTT), Concept development, REST API, the Android operating system, Adaptive Autosar and have worked within the automotive industry.
It’s also meritorious if you have experience in SOME/IP, CAN, security practices, SIL/HIL testing, and working with agile principles.

Specialist: position typically requires 8 years or more relevant experience

Volvo Group is an equal opportunity employer that values diversity in our workplace and we welcome all applicants regardless of age, ethnicity, gender or cultural background.

Job Posting Start Date:   2024-01-08
Job Posting End Date:   2024-06-30
Location:   Göteborg
Job Family:   Elect. & Electr. Embedded Softw. Eng.
Price: 714 sek/h

